/*
Approach:
- Use the two-pointer technique.
- Pointer `i` traverses string `s` (the subsequence).
- Pointer `j` traverses string `t` (the main string).
- Compare the current characters of both strings:
    - If they match, move `i` to the next character in `s`.
    - Always move `j` to the next character in `t`.
- If `j` reaches the end of `t` before all characters of `s` are matched,
  return `false`.
- If all characters of `s` are matched (`i == s.length()`), return `true`.

Time Complexity: O(n)
- `n` = length of `t`
- Each character in `t` is visited at most once.

Space Complexity: O(1)
- Only two pointers are used, so no extra space is required.
*/
class Solution {
    public boolean isSubsequence(String s, String t) {
       int i=0;
       int j=0;
       while(i<s.length()){
        if(j>=t.length()){
            return false;
        }
        if(s.charAt(i)==t.charAt(j)){
            i++;
        }
        j++;
       }
        return true;
    }
   
}